help.topic:
These are nine things you should do when you start your game.
After that, use the rest of this Help as a reference manual.

{{W|1. Walk around}}

{{?KB|Move by pressing directional keys (~CmdMoveN, ~CmdMoveE, etc) or by clicking on the map.}}{{?Gamepad|Indicate direction with ~UI:Navigate and press ~Take A Step to move or hold ~Take A Step to move continuously.}}{{?Gamepad|
You can also auto-explore the map with ~CmdAutoExplore.}}

{{W|2. Interact with things}}

Walk next to an NPC or other object and press ~CmdUse.

{{W|3. Look at things}}

{{?KB|Press }}~CmdLook to enter Look mode and then move the cursor around the map.{{?KB|
Or {{hotkey|right-click}} to quick look.}}

{{W|4. Use your abilities}}

{{?KB|Click on a button on the ability bar at the bottom of your screen
or press its hotkey.}}{{?Gamepad|Navigate the hotbar at the bottom of your screen with ~UI:Navigate/left and ~UI:Navigate/right
and then press ~Use Ability to use an ability.}}

{{W|5. View your character sheet}}

{{?KB|Press ~CmdCharacter to view your core character info.
Press ~CmdEquipment to view your equipment.
Press ~CmdInventory to view your inventory.
Press ~CmdJournal to view your journal.
Press ~CmdQuests to view your quests.
Press ~CmdSkillsPowers to view your skills.
Press ~CmdFactions to view your faction relationships.

You can scroll through these pages with ~Page Left and ~Page Right.}}{{?Gamepad|Press ~CmdCharacter to view your core character info.
Navigate to other pages in your character sheet with ~Page Left and ~Page Right.}}

{{W|6. Bring up a list of points of interest}}

Press ~CmdMoveToPointOfInterest.

{{W|7. Bring up additional information about objects on the map}}

Press ~Highlight for an overlay with extra info like creature hostility 
(red = hostile, yellow = neutral, green = friendly) and a clear view of 
interesting items.

{{W|8. Walk to another map}}

Simply walk offscreen, or go to the world map with ~CmdMoveU.

{{W|9. Attack an enemy}}

To perform a basic attack, just walk into a hostile creature.
Or you can use an attack ability.

